Dialogue: 0,0:00:04.88,0:00:06.80,English,,0,0,0,,Of all the games in my collection,
Dialogue: 0,0:00:06.80,0:00:10.34,English,,0,0,0,,few raise my excitement level at the mere sight of it like this one.
Dialogue: 0,0:00:10.34,0:00:12.72,English,,0,0,0,,Doom II: Hell on Earth,
Dialogue: 0,0:00:12.72,0:00:16.12,English,,0,0,0,,developed by id Software and released to North American retail
Dialogue: 0,0:00:16.12,0:00:20.94,English,,0,0,0,,by GT Interactive Software on October 10th, 1994.
Dialogue: 0,0:00:20.94,0:00:25.44,English,,0,0,0,,Exactly ten months after the shareware release of the original Doom, which was still wildly
Dialogue: 0,0:00:25.44,0:00:29.08,English,,0,0,0,,profitable despite only being sold via phone or mail order.
Dialogue: 0,0:00:29.08,0:00:32.12,English,,0,0,0,,And that’s one reason Doom II happened so quickly
Dialogue: 0,0:00:32.12,0:00:35.88,English,,0,0,0,,publisher GT Interactive really wanted a copy of Doom to sell
Dialogue: 0,0:00:35.88,0:00:38.42,English,,0,0,0,,by the 1994 holiday season.
Dialogue: 0,0:00:38.42,0:00:43.05,English,,0,0,0,,They’d worked with id Software already, having distributed these registered full versions
Dialogue: 0,0:00:43.05,0:00:46.55,English,,0,0,0,,of Commander Keen: Goodbye Galaxy and Wolfenstein 3D.
Dialogue: 0,0:00:46.55,0:00:51.78,English,,0,0,0,,But Doom was another beast entirely, able to rake in $100,000 worth of orders a day
Dialogue: 0,0:00:51.78,0:00:54.37,English,,0,0,0,,without any retail presence whatsoever.
Dialogue: 0,0:00:54.37,0:00:57.91,English,,0,0,0,,To put it bluntly, id Software didn’t need a publisher for Doom.
Dialogue: 0,0:00:57.91,0:01:02.12,English,,0,0,0,,GT was adamant though, and after a couple of meetings that went nowhere,
Dialogue: 0,0:01:02.12,0:01:03.66,English,,0,0,0,,an agreement was reached.
Dialogue: 0,0:01:03.67,0:01:07.96,English,,0,0,0,,Doom II would be developed with a $2 million marketing budget, and id Software would retain
Dialogue: 0,0:01:07.96,0:01:12.15,English,,0,0,0,,all intellectual property rights, creative control, and company branding on the front
Dialogue: 0,0:01:12.15,0:01:13.74,English,,0,0,0,,of the box instead of the back.
Dialogue: 0,0:01:13.74,0:01:16.52,English,,0,0,0,,Another part of this deal was that, unlike the original,
Dialogue: 0,0:01:16.52,0:01:19.50,English,,0,0,0,,Doom II would not get a shareware version at all.
Dialogue: 0,0:01:19.50,0:01:23.82,English,,0,0,0,,Developer John Carmack for one seemed fine with this, stating that “A lot of people
Dialogue: 0,0:01:31.52,0:01:34.08,English,,0,0,0,,{\pos(990,170)}so they’d left the shareware model behind this time.
Dialogue: 0,0:01:34.08,0:01:40.26,English,,0,0,0,,And well that worked out, considering Doom II was the best-selling game of 1994.
Dialogue: 0,0:01:40.27,0:01:45.29,English,,0,0,0,,Demand was so high that its initial print run of 600,000 copies sold out in a single
Dialogue: 0,0:01:45.29,0:01:51.24,English,,0,0,0,,month, with total copies sold surpassing 1.5 million by the end of the ‘90s.
Dialogue: 0,0:01:51.24,0:01:56.09,English,,0,0,0,,And it was this original US release that I first saw around Christmas of ‘94, proudly
Dialogue: 0,0:01:56.09,0:01:59.77,English,,0,0,0,,displayed on a front endcap in the PC gaming section at a local K-Mart.
Dialogue: 0,0:01:59.77,0:02:04.96,English,,0,0,0,,It stood out for a variety of reasons, not the least of which was its box art, painted
Dialogue: 0,0:02:04.96,0:02:07.78,English,,0,0,0,,by acclaimed fantasy artist Gerald Brom.
Dialogue: 0,0:02:07.78,0:02:12.95,English,,0,0,0,,That gruesome cyberdemon with its weird exposed abdomen, Doomguy wielding his shotgun and
Dialogue: 0,0:02:12.95,0:02:16.49,English,,0,0,0,,that utterly bonkers haircut, smashing cinder blocks with his butt.
Dialogue: 0,0:02:16.49,0:02:21.22,English,,0,0,0,,And of course it stood out because dude, it was Doom, Part Two!
Dialogue: 0,0:02:21.22,0:02:25.46,English,,0,0,0,,Something I had no idea existed until I saw it on the shelf for $50,
Dialogue: 0,0:02:25.46,0:02:28.08,English,,0,0,0,,with the original game nowhere in sight.
Dialogue: 0,0:02:28.08,0:02:33.56,English,,0,0,0,,Kinda strange in retrospect, but before Ultimate Doom came around in 1995, the only version
Dialogue: 0,0:02:33.56,0:02:38.20,English,,0,0,0,,of Doom for sale in stores was Doom II, and maybe Doom I shareware.
Dialogue: 0,0:02:38.20,0:02:42.61,English,,0,0,0,,A fact that seemed to cause some confusion if these newspaper ads are any indication,
Dialogue: 0,0:02:42.61,0:02:45.16,English,,0,0,0,,check out this mixup by Staples. Whoops.
Dialogue: 0,0:02:45.44,0:02:50.12,English,,0,0,0,,Doom II was also the first time I’d seen this new thing called an ESRB rating, this
Dialogue: 0,0:02:50.12,0:02:52.73,English,,0,0,0,,imposing black and white ‘M’ on the box.
Dialogue: 0,0:02:52.73,0:02:57.88,English,,0,0,0,,Yep, this hit shortly after the big video game ratings debate in the US, and Doom II
Dialogue: 0,0:02:57.88,0:03:01.22,English,,0,0,0,,was one of the first to earn itself a Mature rating.
Dialogue: 0,0:03:01.22,0:03:05.14,English,,0,0,0,,Something not seen on the UK release distributed by Virgin Software,
Dialogue: 0,0:03:05.14,0:03:08.34,English,,0,0,0,,lending this particular cover a cleaner overall look.
Dialogue: 0,0:03:08.74,0:03:14.14,English,,0,0,0,,Then again, it doesn’t have that shiny, embossed cardboard that the American one has, so eh.
Dialogue: 0,0:03:14.14,0:03:17.74,English,,0,0,0,,You win some you lose some in the worldwide Doom II box art department.
Dialogue: 0,0:03:17.75,0:03:21.19,English,,0,0,0,,Anyway, enough persnickety packaging ponderment!
Dialogue: 0,0:03:21.19,0:03:26.78,English,,0,0,0,,Inside the box you get Doom II itself on either a CD-ROM or a quintet of 3.5” high density
Dialogue: 0,0:03:26.78,0:03:30.25,English,,0,0,0,,floppy disks, with each format sold as its own SKU.
Dialogue: 0,0:03:30.25,0:03:34.97,English,,0,0,0,,There’s also this 8-page manual addendum booklet with plenty of DOS-related setup tips
Dialogue: 0,0:03:34.97,0:03:37.59,English,,0,0,0,,and frequently asked troubleshooting questions.
Dialogue: 0,0:03:37.59,0:03:43.39,English,,0,0,0,,And then there’s the Doom II instruction manual, with 14 full-color pages of backstory,
Dialogue: 0,0:03:43.39,0:03:47.97,English,,0,0,0,,gameplay tips, and listings for each weapon, item, and enemy in the game.
Dialogue: 0,0:03:47.97,0:03:51.74,English,,0,0,0,,Fantastic stuff, but I’m beyond ready to play now so let’s get to it!
Dialogue: 0,0:03:52.30,0:03:58.84,English,,0,0,0,,Doom II for DOS starts off the same as its predecessor: a vivid 256-color splash screen
Dialogue: 0,0:03:58.84,0:04:03.08,English,,0,0,0,,with depictions of demonic destruction and some overly ominous music.
Dialogue: 0,0:04:10.84,0:04:12.36,English,,0,0,0,,That's just the Sound Blaster version.
Dialogue: 0,0:04:12.36,0:04:16.22,English,,0,0,0,,It also supports the Roland Sound Canvas and other MIDI devices of course,
Dialogue: 0,0:04:16.22,0:04:18.42,English,,0,0,0,,but there’s something about the combo of Doom
Dialogue: 0,0:04:18.42,0:04:20.96,English,,0,0,0,,and Bobby Prince’s creepy OPL3 music
Dialogue: 0,0:04:20.96,0:04:22.66,English,,0,0,0,,that makes me the happiest.
Dialogue: 0,0:04:22.66,0:04:27.34,English,,0,0,0,,From here you can start a new game by selecting your difficulty, and... that’s it!
Dialogue: 0,0:04:27.34,0:04:32.36,English,,0,0,0,,No episodes to choose from this time, instead it’s a continuous 30-level campaign.
Dialogue: 0,0:04:32.36,0:04:36.94,English,,0,0,0,,Straight away the action begins, with a pistol in your hand and zombies in your sights.
Dialogue: 0,0:04:44.36,0:04:48.14,English,,0,0,0,,Or you could take the opportunity to look around and soak in the environment, which
Dialogue: 0,0:04:48.15,0:04:52.81,English,,0,0,0,,inevitably brings your attention to this spot over to the left hiding the chainsaw.
Dialogue: 0,0:04:52.81,0:04:55.04,English,,0,0,0,,Yeah I pretty much always go chainsaw.
Dialogue: 0,0:05:03.42,0:05:07.40,English,,0,0,0,,If you’re paying attention, by the end of level one you’ll have a pistol, a chainsaw,
Dialogue: 0,0:05:07.40,0:05:11.30,English,,0,0,0,,a shotgun, a rocket launcher, a bunch of armor, and full health.
Dialogue: 0,0:05:11.30,0:05:16.38,English,,0,0,0,,Armed to the teeth after the very first level, that’s the Doom II experience right there.
Dialogue: 0,0:05:18.42,0:05:23.04,English,,0,0,0,,You’re prepped for the upcoming slaughter right off the bat, with Doomguy boasting speed,
Dialogue: 0,0:05:23.04,0:05:27.94,English,,0,0,0,,agility, and overall control that remains as satisfying as it was in the original Doom.
Dialogue: 0,0:05:27.94,0:05:32.75,English,,0,0,0,,No surprise since Doom II is built on the same tech and pretty much acts as a standalone
Dialogue: 0,0:05:32.75,0:05:34.62,English,,0,0,0,,expansion pack to the original game.
Dialogue: 0,0:05:34.62,0:05:40.28,English,,0,0,0,,It has the same 2.5D id Tech 1 engine running underneath, the same technical limitations
Dialogue: 0,0:05:40.28,0:05:43.74,English,,0,0,0,,in terms of not being able to look up or down or have rooms over rooms.
Dialogue: 0,0:05:43.74,0:05:45.94,English,,0,0,0,,There’s no jumping, no vertical aiming,
Dialogue: 0,0:05:45.94,0:05:49.00,English,,0,0,0,,no special moves to pull off or skill trees to unlock.
Dialogue: 0,0:05:49.00,0:05:51.52,English,,0,0,0,,And that’s all awesome in my book.
Dialogue: 0,0:05:51.52,0:05:57.16,English,,0,0,0,,Shoot demons, find key cards, unlock doors and secret rooms, find more key cards, reach
Dialogue: 0,0:05:57.16,0:06:01.59,English,,0,0,0,,the exit and move onto the next level to do it all again until you reach the end boss.
Dialogue: 0,0:06:01.59,0:06:04.90,English,,0,0,0,,Well-balanced FPS goodness, so why fix what ain’t broke?
Dialogue: 0,0:06:05.18,0:06:09.32,English,,0,0,0,,Because unbroken things can always be fixed with more guns, I guess.
Dialogue: 0,0:06:09.32,0:06:11.78,English,,0,0,0,,This was made in Texas, after all.
Dialogue: 0,0:06:11.78,0:06:17.56,English,,0,0,0,,Yeah it’s time we talk about Doom II’s big fat arsenal: truly one of the great joys in life.
Dialogue: 0,0:06:17.56,0:06:22.18,English,,0,0,0,,Beyond the aforementioned fist, chainsaw, pistol, shotgun, and rocket launcher, also
Dialogue: 0,0:06:22.18,0:06:27.43,English,,0,0,0,,making a triumphant return is the chaingun, with its rapid fire room-clearing abilities
Dialogue: 0,0:06:27.43,0:06:30.69,English,,0,0,0,,proving as useful as ever against enemies near and far.
Dialogue: 0,0:06:30.69,0:06:35.61,English,,0,0,0,,There’s also the plasma gun, frantically firing energy cells as quickly as the original
Dialogue: 0,0:06:35.61,0:06:38.74,English,,0,0,0,,Doom, but popping up far earlier this time, on the fifth map.
Dialogue: 0,0:06:38.74,0:06:43.38,English,,0,0,0,,And of course, it isn’t Doom without the BFG, and again you can find it faster this
Dialogue: 0,0:06:43.38,0:06:47.12,English,,0,0,0,,time, with level eight and onward becoming your personal playground
Dialogue: 0,0:06:47.12,0:06:49.52,English,,0,0,0,,of glowing green plasmic destruction.
Dialogue: 0,0:06:49.52,0:06:52.14,English,,0,0,0,,And then, ohh-ho-ho, and then.
Dialogue: 0,0:06:52.14,0:06:56.06,English,,0,0,0,,We’ve got the one and only, the often imitated but never duplicated,
Dialogue: 0,0:06:56.06,0:06:58.04,English,,0,0,0,,double-barreled Super Shotgun.
Dialogue: 0,0:07:07.10,0:07:10.90,English,,0,0,0,,Introduced near the beginning of level two, this monster of a weapon
Dialogue: 0,0:07:10.90,0:07:13.04,English,,0,0,0,,is pure triple-filtered bliss.
Dialogue: 0,0:07:13.04,0:07:16.91,English,,0,0,0,,Sure it takes twice the ammunition as the regular shotty, but it’s more than twenty
Dialogue: 0,0:07:16.91,0:07:21.30,English,,0,0,0,,times as satisfying so the trade off is a no-brainer.
Dialogue: 0,0:07:21.30,0:07:25.24,English,,0,0,0,,Just two metal barrels held together with a piece of wood and explosives in the middle,
Dialogue: 0,0:07:25.24,0:07:29.72,English,,0,0,0,,it undersells itself on aesthetics and completely over-delivers on power.
Dialogue: 0,0:07:29.72,0:07:33.93,English,,0,0,0,,More often than not, a single well-positioned shot is all it takes, and that’s for the
Dialogue: 0,0:07:33.93,0:07:36.74,English,,0,0,0,,majority of the enemies in the entire campaign.
Dialogue: 0,0:07:38.06,0:07:40.12,English,,0,0,0,,It’s little wonder why it’s called the Super Shotgun,
Dialogue: 0,0:07:40.12,0:07:41.66,English,,0,0,0,,because that’s just what it is!
Dialogue: 0,0:07:41.66,0:07:44.30,English,,0,0,0,,Though I suppose technically it’s the combat shotgun,
Dialogue: 0,0:07:44.30,0:07:46.90,English,,0,0,0,,going by the included documentation, but
Dialogue: 0,0:07:46.90,0:07:51.02,English,,0,0,0,,Eh that term brings to mind a whole ‘nother category of semi-autos and self-loaders, so
Dialogue: 0,0:07:51.03,0:07:56.15,English,,0,0,0,,I’m glad they gave this side-by-side a more appropriately super name in the actual game.
Dialogue: 0,0:07:56.15,0:08:00.02,English,,0,0,0,,And what good is a big bad new weapon without a big bad new lineup of satanic minions
Dialogue: 0,0:08:00.02,0:08:01.50,English,,0,0,0,,to shoot in the face?
Dialogue: 0,0:08:01.50,0:08:05.91,English,,0,0,0,,Doom’s original ten monsters were pretty great, and they’re all still around, including
Dialogue: 0,0:08:05.91,0:08:09.91,English,,0,0,0,,creatures like the Cyberdemon that used to be bosses but now just show up to ruin your
Dialogue: 0,0:08:09.91,0:08:11.65,English,,0,0,0,,day throughout the whole game.
Dialogue: 0,0:08:11.65,0:08:16.37,English,,0,0,0,,But Doom II rounds out the enemy roster by doubling down on demons, and as a result it
Dialogue: 0,0:08:16.37,0:08:18.54,English,,0,0,0,,really feels like the whole gang’s here now.
Dialogue: 0,0:08:18.54,0:08:22.69,English,,0,0,0,,The Heavy Weapon Dude wields a chaingun and can absolutely wreck your life if you’re
Dialogue: 0,0:08:22.69,0:08:25.30,English,,0,0,0,,not careful, that hit-scanning is no joke.
Dialogue: 0,0:08:25.30,0:08:29.78,English,,0,0,0,,Hell Knights are like weaker, tanner versions of the old barons of hell, nothing terribly
Dialogue: 0,0:08:29.78,0:08:32.14,English,,0,0,0,,threatening so I welcome the target practice.
Dialogue: 0,0:08:32.14,0:08:37.06,English,,0,0,0,,The Mancubus is a big old blob of terror with dual flamethrowers and a whole lotta hitpoints,
Dialogue: 0,0:08:37.06,0:08:39.30,English,,0,0,0,,slow but effectively nasty.
Dialogue: 0,0:08:39.30,0:08:44.14,English,,0,0,0,,Arachnotrons are versions of the old spider demon, this time much smaller and shooting
Dialogue: 0,0:08:44.14,0:08:47.78,English,,0,0,0,,blasts of green energy, which are thankfully easily dodged.
Dialogue: 0,0:08:47.78,0:08:53.19,English,,0,0,0,,And Pain Elementals, now these just suck, being another floating blob like the Cacodemon,
Dialogue: 0,0:08:53.19,0:08:56.39,English,,0,0,0,,but spitting out lost souls instead of ball lightning.
Dialogue: 0,0:08:56.39,0:08:59.58,English,,0,0,0,,Way more annoying due to that, what a pain...
Dialogue: 0,0:08:59.92,0:09:00.86,English,,0,0,0,,elemental.
Dialogue: 0,0:09:00.86,0:09:04.14,English,,0,0,0,,Then you’ve got the Revenant, a tall lumbering skeleton beast
Dialogue: 0,0:09:04.14,0:09:07.02,English,,0,0,0,,with shoulder-mounted rocket launchers and blood for pants.
Dialogue: 0,0:09:07.02,0:09:11.28,English,,0,0,0,,Not too hard to kill, but its rockets are basically homing missiles, so there’s that.
Dialogue: 0,0:09:11.28,0:09:16.46,English,,0,0,0,,And finally, there’s the big daddy chaos bastard of Doom II, the Arch-vile, which is
Dialogue: 0,0:09:16.46,0:09:19.94,English,,0,0,0,,not only terrifying to look at, but deadly to look at as well.
Dialogue: 0,0:09:19.94,0:09:23.87,English,,0,0,0,,Simply making line of sight contact with the thing can result in you being set on fire
Dialogue: 0,0:09:23.87,0:09:26.70,English,,0,0,0,,until you explode, which is not ideal.
Dialogue: 0,0:09:26.70,0:09:31.14,English,,0,0,0,,Arch-viles can also bring lower-tier enemies back from the dead if you let them stick around
Dialogue: 0,0:09:31.14,0:09:32.77,English,,0,0,0,,long, so don’t do that.
Dialogue: 0,0:09:32.77,0:09:34.52,English,,0,0,0,,Kill ‘em hard, kill ‘em fast.
Dialogue: 0,0:09:34.52,0:09:38.88,English,,0,0,0,,Oh yeah, and there’s a couple secret levels that include killable Commander Keens hung
Dialogue: 0,0:09:38.88,0:09:42.83,English,,0,0,0,,from the ceiling, and even SS troops from Wolfenstein 3D.
Dialogue: 0,0:09:42.83,0:09:47.16,English,,0,0,0,,But these are more like easter egg/in-joke kinda things, you won’t be seeing any keens
Dialogue: 0,0:09:47.16,0:09:50.90,English,,0,0,0,,or nazis wandering around the streets of Earth or the spaceports of Mars.
Dialogue: 0,0:09:50.90,0:09:55.46,English,,0,0,0,,Speaking of which, another thing to touch on are the levels themselves, the atmosphere
Dialogue: 0,0:09:55.46,0:09:59.13,English,,0,0,0,,they provide, and the overall pacing throughout the 30-level campaign.
Dialogue: 0,0:09:59.13,0:10:04.16,English,,0,0,0,,Because, well, this is where Doom II is kind of a mixed bag in my opinion.
Dialogue: 0,0:10:04.16,0:10:06.52,English,,0,0,0,,Don’t get me wrong, it’s still a really well-made bag
Dialogue: 0,0:10:06.52,0:10:09.04,English,,0,0,0,,filled with all sorts of fun goodies to play with.
Dialogue: 0,0:10:09.04,0:10:13.70,English,,0,0,0,,It’s just that inside the bag are a couple of questionable pockets filled with odd-shaped
Dialogue: 0,0:10:13.70,0:10:16.64,English,,0,0,0,,doohickies that you don’t quite know what to make of.
Dialogue: 0,0:10:16.64,0:10:21.49,English,,0,0,0,,My biggest qualm is that around a quarter of the levels are rather unappealing to me,
Dialogue: 0,0:10:21.49,0:10:24.62,English,,0,0,0,,specifically the ones that are supposed to be based in our realm.
Dialogue: 0,0:10:24.62,0:10:29.70,English,,0,0,0,,I mean, for a game titled Hell on Earth, I expected a lot more Earth, with like,
Dialogue: 0,0:10:29.70,0:10:31.20,English,,0,0,0,,hell on it and stuff.
Dialogue: 0,0:10:31.20,0:10:35.32,English,,0,0,0,,Instead we’ve got a barely-connected selection of levels that are loosely sanctioned off
Dialogue: 0,0:10:35.33,0:10:39.38,English,,0,0,0,,into three episodes: The Space Station, The City, and Hell.
Dialogue: 0,0:10:39.38,0:10:44.02,English,,0,0,0,,Again, for the most part I have a lot of fun playing Doom II, over and over again.
Dialogue: 0,0:10:44.02,0:10:48.27,English,,0,0,0,,Martian space stations and pixelated hellscapes, aw yeah, gimme more of that!
Dialogue: 0,0:10:48.27,0:10:52.88,English,,0,0,0,,But then you’ve got levels like Downtown that just... what is this?
Dialogue: 0,0:10:52.88,0:10:54.90,English,,0,0,0,,Props for trying something new I guess,
Dialogue: 0,0:10:54.90,0:10:58.96,English,,0,0,0,,a metropolitan area and skyscrapers in the Doom engine is kinda neat.
Dialogue: 0,0:10:58.96,0:11:04.10,English,,0,0,0,,But it’s a slog to navigate and there are far too many enemies right above your line of sight.
Dialogue: 0,0:11:04.10,0:11:08.93,English,,0,0,0,,Then there are maps that largely exist to promote some level design gimmick, like Tricks
Dialogue: 0,0:11:08.93,0:11:11.67,English,,0,0,0,,and Traps, The Chasm, and Barrels o’ Fun.
Dialogue: 0,0:11:11.67,0:11:16.20,English,,0,0,0,,Stuff like monster infighting, teleporter logic, tricky platforms, skinny walkways,
Dialogue: 0,0:11:16.20,0:11:20.88,English,,0,0,0,,hundreds of explosive barrels strung together, it’s like being stuck in a lab experiment.
Dialogue: 0,0:11:20.88,0:11:24.28,English,,0,0,0,,Maps like these are bizarre, sorely sticking out from the rest.
Dialogue: 0,0:11:24.28,0:11:28.26,English,,0,0,0,,I don’t wanna call out any particular level designer here (Sandy Petersen)
Dialogue: 0,0:11:28.26,0:11:32.61,English,,0,0,0,,but the more I’ve played these maps over the years, the more I dread enduring them again.
Dialogue: 0,0:11:32.61,0:11:35.10,English,,0,0,0,,That's not to say all the new map styles fall flat, though.
Dialogue: 0,0:11:35.10,0:11:40.38,English,,0,0,0,,There’s a lot more experimentation than Doom 1 with enemy quantity and wide-open spaces,
Dialogue: 0,0:11:40.38,0:11:44.83,English,,0,0,0,,enabling these ridiculous battles with dozens of demons attacking, screaming, dying, and
Dialogue: 0,0:11:44.83,0:11:48.70,English,,0,0,0,,in-fighting while you circle strafe around picking them off, I love this stuff.
Dialogue: 0,0:12:03.26,0:12:08.17,English,,0,0,0,,A side effect of these larger, densely-packed levels is that the performance suffered on
Dialogue: 0,0:12:08.17,0:12:12.61,English,,0,0,0,,lower-end machines back in ‘94, leading to higher system requirements for Doom II
Dialogue: 0,0:12:12.61,0:12:13.88,English,,0,0,0,,compared to the original.
Dialogue: 0,0:12:13.88,0:12:17.30,English,,0,0,0,,What better reason to grab a 486 Overdrive though, right?
Dialogue: 0,0:12:17.30,0:12:22.04,English,,0,0,0,,Some levels also play with darkness to an excessive degree, making for one fittingly
Dialogue: 0,0:12:22.04,0:12:25.92,English,,0,0,0,,foreboding atmosphere, and granting greater justification for the existence
Dialogue: 0,0:12:25.92,0:12:27.94,English,,0,0,0,,of the Light Amplification Visor.
Dialogue: 0,0:12:27.94,0:12:32.83,English,,0,0,0,,However, the creep factor is somewhat lessened by your amped-up firepower, not to mention
Dialogue: 0,0:12:32.83,0:12:36.82,English,,0,0,0,,the new Megasphere that boosts your health and armor to 200%.
Dialogue: 0,0:12:36.82,0:12:40.20,English,,0,0,0,,It’s dark, sure, but not to the point of unfairness.
Dialogue: 0,0:12:40.20,0:12:44.62,English,,0,0,0,,Anyway yeah, even though the occasional map design makes me scratch my head in bewilderment,
Dialogue: 0,0:12:44.62,0:12:48.26,English,,0,0,0,,the overall Doom II experience is one that I cherish.
Dialogue: 0,0:12:48.26,0:12:52.08,English,,0,0,0,,And I freely admit that the super shotgun silliness has a lot to do with it,
Dialogue: 0,0:12:52.08,0:12:54.42,English,,0,0,0,,as arguably overpowered as it is.
Dialogue: 0,0:12:54.42,0:12:57.18,English,,0,0,0,,But it’s just too enjoyable for me to care!
Dialogue: 0,0:12:57.18,0:13:00.77,English,,0,0,0,,Maybe it’s another story dealing with it in multiplayer deathmatch, but the main draw
Dialogue: 0,0:13:00.77,0:13:04.31,English,,0,0,0,,for me is the single player so I’m all for it.
Dialogue: 0,0:13:04.31,0:13:09.24,English,,0,0,0,,Then you add in the expanded bestiary of baddies and huge retail presence, and it makes sense
Dialogue: 0,0:13:09.24,0:13:12.95,English,,0,0,0,,that Doom II took off in a way that even its predecessor never did.
Dialogue: 0,0:13:12.95,0:13:17.63,English,,0,0,0,,And I’m talking strictly in terms of community engagement, not like, sheer quantity of installations
Dialogue: 0,0:13:17.63,0:13:19.49,English,,0,0,0,,or overall cultural relevance.
Dialogue: 0,0:13:19.49,0:13:24.73,English,,0,0,0,,Obviously Doom 1 has its place in history, but Doom II is the one that formed such strong
Dialogue: 0,0:13:24.73,0:13:27.83,English,,0,0,0,,community bonds that remain active to this day.
Dialogue: 0,0:13:27.83,0:13:32.74,English,,0,0,0,,The sheer number of custom maps and total conversion WADs made for it is staggering,
Dialogue: 0,0:13:32.74,0:13:35.01,English,,0,0,0,,both back then and into the present.
Dialogue: 0,0:13:35.01,0:13:39.99,English,,0,0,0,,And the proliferation of them has only increased since the source code was released in 1997,
Dialogue: 0,0:13:39.99,0:13:45.38,English,,0,0,0,,resulting in source ports and fan-made upgrades like GLDoom, ZDoom, Boom, Chocolate Doom,
Dialogue: 0,0:13:45.38,0:13:47.80,English,,0,0,0,,Skulltag, Zandronum, and beyond.
Dialogue: 0,0:13:47.80,0:13:52.02,English,,0,0,0,,I’m currently quite fond of Crispy Doom in particular, for when I want to play on
Dialogue: 0,0:13:52.02,0:13:56.31,English,,0,0,0,,a modern machine instead of original hardware, and find myself wanting a few extra quality
Dialogue: 0,0:13:56.31,0:13:59.33,English,,0,0,0,,of life improvements without ruining the original feel of the game.
Dialogue: 0,0:13:59.33,0:14:04.01,English,,0,0,0,,And then there was the retail side of things, with Doom II expansions and addons hitting
Dialogue: 0,0:14:04.01,0:14:06.85,English,,0,0,0,,shelves for years after its 1994 launch.
Dialogue: 0,0:14:06.85,0:14:13.29,English,,0,0,0,,The first official one being Master Levels for Doom II in 1995, consisting of 20 WADs
Dialogue: 0,0:14:13.29,0:14:17.18,English,,0,0,0,,promising to be masterfully-made, and nearly three thousand fan-made maps
Dialogue: 0,0:14:17.18,0:14:19.24,English,,0,0,0,,downloaded from the fledgling internet.
Dialogue: 0,0:14:19.24,0:14:23.46,English,,0,0,0,,Also has this rather radical poster expanding on the box art.
Dialogue: 0,0:14:23.47,0:14:28.82,English,,0,0,0,,Then there was Final Doom in 1996, an officially licensed standalone product featuring two
Dialogue: 0,0:14:28.82,0:14:32.74,English,,0,0,0,,new episodes, TNT: Evilution and Plutonia Experiment,
Dialogue: 0,0:14:32.74,0:14:36.46,English,,0,0,0,,and which was in reality far from the actual final Doom.
Dialogue: 0,0:14:36.46,0:14:42.62,English,,0,0,0,,Because next was the Depths of Doom Trilogy in 1997, packing Ultimate Doom, Doom II, and
Dialogue: 0,0:14:42.62,0:14:45.11,English,,0,0,0,,Master Levels into one beefy big box package.
Dialogue: 0,0:14:45.11,0:14:48.98,English,,0,0,0,,There’s also been a slew of repackages and re-releases since then, with one of the more
Dialogue: 0,0:14:48.98,0:14:54.62,English,,0,0,0,,interesting being Doom II to Xbox 360, which introduced No Rest For The Living, an all
Dialogue: 0,0:14:54.62,0:14:57.26,English,,0,0,0,,new expansion episode by Nerve Software.
Dialogue: 0,0:14:57.26,0:14:59.74,English,,0,0,0,,It’s pretty good stuff actually, I recommend it!
Dialogue: 0,0:14:59.75,0:15:04.52,English,,0,0,0,,The episode has subsequently shown up in the Doom 3 BFG Edition, which itself includes
Dialogue: 0,0:15:04.52,0:15:09.60,English,,0,0,0,,Doom II, and can also be played using a source port with the right WAD file.
Dialogue: 0,0:15:09.60,0:15:14.48,English,,0,0,0,,And that’s not to mention the whole unlicensed scene, with third-party publishers like WizardWorks
Dialogue: 0,0:15:14.48,0:15:20.67,English,,0,0,0,,releasing at least half a dozen map compilations in their D!Zone series starting in 1995.
Dialogue: 0,0:15:20.67,0:15:25.85,English,,0,0,0,,Doom II was its own gaming ecosystem throughout the mid-90s, with stuff sold in stores, distributed
Dialogue: 0,0:15:25.85,0:15:29.75,English,,0,0,0,,online, shared among friends, and even created by the US government.
Dialogue: 0,0:15:29.75,0:15:32.48,English,,0,0,0,,Yeah, Marine Doom was a thing, an official project
Dialogue: 0,0:15:32.48,0:15:36.48,English,,0,0,0,,of the United States Marine Corps Modeling and Simulation Management Office.
Dialogue: 0,0:15:36.48,0:15:39.36,English,,0,0,0,,Hehe, ahh the 90s were wild man.
Dialogue: 0,0:15:40.22,0:15:42.52,English,,0,0,0,,And that, folks, is Doom II.
Dialogue: 0,0:15:42.92,0:15:47.20,English,,0,0,0,,As far as projects go that were slapped together in less than a year, instigated by the financial
Dialogue: 0,0:15:47.20,0:15:49.30,English,,0,0,0,,incentives of a hungry retail publisher?
Dialogue: 0,0:15:49.30,0:15:53.51,English,,0,0,0,,Yeah, it could’ve sucked, but thankfully id Software did what they did back then and
Dialogue: 0,0:15:53.51,0:15:56.58,English,,0,0,0,,made something excellent on their terms.
Dialogue: 0,0:15:56.58,0:16:01.70,English,,0,0,0,,The way I see it, Doom II took what Doom did and ran with it, fleshing out the experience
Dialogue: 0,0:16:01.70,0:16:03.64,English,,0,0,0,,and cementing its reputation.
Dialogue: 0,0:16:03.64,0:16:08.14,English,,0,0,0,,It’s hard to imagine the series without Revenants and Super Shotguns.
Dialogue: 0,0:16:08.14,0:16:12.22,English,,0,0,0,,Or shooting a giant wall demon that actually hides John Romero’s head on a stake.
Dialogue: 0,0:16:12.22,0:16:18.24,English,,0,0,0,,And yet for a time, these were nowhere to be found, and reality was worse off for it.
Dialogue: 0,0:16:18.24,0:16:21.85,English,,0,0,0,,Doom II made Doom more Doom-like than ever before,
Dialogue: 0,0:16:21.86,0:16:24.54,English,,0,0,0,,and even with its flaws, I love it nonetheless.
Dialogue: 0,0:16:39.24,0:16:43.26,English,,0,0,0,,And if you liked this then perhaps check out my other Doom-related stuff right here.
Dialogue: 0,0:16:43.26,0:16:47.44,English,,0,0,0,,Or maybe even subscribe, I release new videos each week here on LGR.
Dialogue: 0,0:16:47.44,0:16:50.14,English,,0,0,0,,And as always, thank you very much for watching!
Dialogue: 0,0:00:04.88,0:00:06.80,Chinese,,0,0,0,,在我收藏的所有游戏中
Dialogue: 0,0:00:06.80,0:00:10.34,Chinese,,0,0,0,,很少有游戏能像这个勾我的魂儿
Dialogue: 0,0:00:10.34,0:00:12.72,Chinese,,0,0,0,,Doom II: Hell on Earth（毁灭战士二：地狱上凡）
Dialogue: 0,0:00:12.72,0:00:16.12,Chinese,,0,0,0,,由id Software开发，在北美
Dialogue: 0,0:00:16.12,0:00:20.94,Chinese,,0,0,0,,由GT Interactive Software在1994.10.10发行
Dialogue: 0,0:00:20.94,0:00:25.44,Chinese,,0,0,0,,他们正好在原版《毁灭战士》发行十个月后趁热打铁
Dialogue: 0,0:00:25.44,0:00:29.08,Chinese,,0,0,0,,就算原版《毁灭战士》仅仅通过电话或邮件订货就能收益颇丰
Dialogue: 0,0:00:29.08,0:00:32.12,Chinese,,0,0,0,,而这也就算为什么《毁灭战士二代》能这么快就能发行
Dialogue: 0,0:00:32.12,0:00:35.88,Chinese,,0,0,0,,发行商GT Interactive十分希望在1994年假期档
Dialogue: 0,0:00:35.88,0:00:38.42,Chinese,,0,0,0,,赶紧发行个《毁灭战士》续集
Dialogue: 0,0:00:38.42,0:00:43.05,Chinese,,0,0,0,,他们在之前已经和id Software合作过了，而且已经发行过了
Dialogue: 0,0:00:43.05,0:00:46.55,Chinese,,0,0,0,,完整版Commander Keen: Goodbye Galaxy和《德军总部3D》
Dialogue: 0,0:00:46.55,0:00:51.78,Chinese,,0,0,0,,但是《毁灭战士二代》又是一个热门，在零售还没开始的情况下
Dialogue: 0,0:00:51.78,0:00:54.37,Chinese,,0,0,0,,一天就预售了十万美元！
Dialogue: 0,0:00:54.37,0:00:57.91,Chinese,,0,0,0,,id Software不想找发行商发行，因为他们像直接获利
Dialogue: 0,0:00:57.91,0:01:02.12,Chinese,,0,0,0,,然而GT坚持发行，所以在几次{\s1}小黑屋{\s0}py交易之后
Dialogue: 0,0:01:02.12,0:01:03.66,Chinese,,0,0,0,,他们达成了协议
Dialogue: 0,0:01:03.67,0:01:07.96,Chinese,,0,0,0,,《毁灭战士二代》的宣传将会有两百万的预算，而且
Dialogue: 0,0:01:07.96,0:01:12.15,Chinese,,0,0,0,,开发商将会拥有软件的所有权，艺术品所有权
Dialogue: 0,0:01:12.15,0:01:13.74,Chinese,,0,0,0,,而且必须在包装盒的正面，而不是背面，打上开发公司标志
Dialogue: 0,0:01:13.74,0:01:16.52,Chinese,,0,0,0,,协议中还有一点，不像原版《毁灭战士》那样
Dialogue: 0,0:01:16.52,0:01:19.50,Chinese,,0,0,0,,《毁灭战士二代》没有免费版本
Dialogue: 0,0:01:19.50,0:01:23.82,Chinese,,0,0,0,,开发者之一John Carmack对这个十分满意，他说：
Dialogue: 0,0:01:23.82,0:01:28.85,Chinese,,0,0,0,,{\pos(990,180)}很多人把免费版本的《毁灭战士》打完后\N就认为他们已经“把毁灭战士通关了”
Dialogue: 0,0:01:28.85,0:01:31.52,Chinese,,0,0,0,,{\pos(990,130)}《毁灭战士二代》将完全是商业产品
Dialogue: 0,0:01:31.52,0:01:34.08,Chinese,,0,0,0,,{\pos(990,122)}所以他们这次没有想过发行免费版游戏
Dialogue: 0,0:01:34.08,0:01:40.26,Chinese,,0,0,0,,然后他们想的没错，《毁灭战士二代》是1994年的畅销游戏
Dialogue: 0,0:01:40.27,0:01:45.29,Chinese,,0,0,0,,这个游戏过于畅销，以至于一天之内首批六十万份游戏
Dialogue: 0,0:01:45.29,0:01:51.24,Chinese,,0,0,0,,便抢购一空，整个九十年代更是卖了创纪录的150万份
Dialogue: 0,0:01:51.24,0:01:56.09,Chinese,,0,0,0,,我在94年圣诞假期时就看见了美首版，就在当地K-Mart的
Dialogue: 0,0:01:56.09,0:01:59.77,Chinese,,0,0,0,,电脑游戏区最前面的摆台前熠熠生辉
Dialogue: 0,0:01:59.77,0:02:04.96,Chinese,,0,0,0,,它在众多游戏前脱颖而出的原因是多样的，不仅是它鲜艳的
Dialogue: 0,0:02:04.96,0:02:07.78,Chinese,,0,0,0,,封面，由盛名远扬的幻想派画家Gerald Brom绘制
Dialogue: 0,0:02:07.78,0:02:12.95,Chinese,,0,0,0,,吓人的Cyberdemon展示着它恐怖的暴露腹部，而Doomguy挥舞着
Dialogue: 0,0:02:12.95,0:02:16.49,Chinese,,0,0,0,,他的猎枪和狗啃的发型，一屁股就把下面的煤渣给坐碎了
Dialogue: 0,0:02:16.49,0:02:21.22,Chinese,,0,0,0,,当然，这还不足以抓人眼球，这可是《毁灭战士》啊！还是二代啊！
Dialogue: 0,0:02:21.22,0:02:25.46,Chinese,,0,0,0,,一开始我没反映过来，直到我看见它卖50美元
Dialogue: 0,0:02:25.46,0:02:28.08,Chinese,,0,0,0,,而且原版《毁灭战士》也没有找到:-（
Dialogue: 0,0:02:28.08,0:02:33.56,Chinese,,0,0,0,,现在想起来还是觉得奇怪，但是在1995年《终极毁灭战士》上市前
Dialogue: 0,0:02:33.56,0:02:38.20,Chinese,,0,0,0,,市面上你能买到的只有《毁灭战士二代》，也许还有原版《毁灭战士》
Dialogue: 0,0:02:38.20,0:02:42.61,Chinese,,0,0,0,,实际上当时报纸上打的广告由于搞错封面，造成了许多误会
Dialogue: 0,0:02:43.29,0:02:45.16,Chinese,,0,0,0,,看看Staples报纸上打的广告吧:-P
Dialogue: 0,0:02:45.44,0:02:50.12,Chinese,,0,0,0,,《毁灭战士二代》也是我看见的的第一个有ESRB评级的游戏
Dialogue: 0,0:02:50.12,0:02:52.73,Chinese,,0,0,0,,盒子上有这个醒目的黑白的M标志
Dialogue: 0,0:02:50.12,0:02:52.73,Comments,,0,0,0,,注：年龄限制：17岁及以上
Dialogue: 0,0:02:52.73,0:02:57.88,Chinese,,0,0,0,,是的，这个就在席卷美国全国的电子游戏讨论之后发行
Dialogue: 0,0:02:52.73,0:02:57.88,Comments,,0,0,0,,注：咱们啥时候游戏也能这样分级，玩游戏本身不会导致青少年不学好
Dialogue: 0,0:02:57.88,0:03:01.22,Chinese,,0,0,0,,而这个游戏也是第一个获得M级（成人级）的游戏
Dialogue: 0,0:03:01.22,0:03:05.14,Chinese,,0,0,0,,而英版游戏，由维珍游戏发行，在包装方面有所缩水
Dialogue: 0,0:03:01.22,0:03:05.14,Comments,,0,0,0,,{\fnComic Sans MS\fs55}Recommed Virgin Record Music: \NOmmadawn - Mike Oldfield\N Phaedra - Tangerine Dream\NNevermind the Bullocks Here's the {\b1}Sex Pistols{\b0}
Dialogue: 0,0:03:05.14,0:03:08.34,Chinese,,0,0,0,,让包装看上去更加平实
Dialogue: 0,0:03:08.74,0:03:14.14,Chinese,,0,0,0,,这个再一次地，没有像美版那样，有抛光和浮雕，所以呢
Dialogue: 0,0:03:14.14,0:03:17.74,Chinese,,0,0,0,,各地的《毁灭战士》包装都互有优劣:-|
Dialogue: 0,0:03:17.75,0:03:21.19,Chinese,,0,0,0,,无论如何，包装大家也看腻了，
Dialogue: 0,0:03:21.19,0:03:26.78,Chinese,,0,0,0,,盒子里面装的就是《毁灭战士二代》游戏了，不是装在CD上
Dialogue: 0,0:03:26.78,0:03:30.25,Chinese,,0,0,0,,就是装在软盘上，每种包装都是不同的条码
Dialogue: 0,0:03:30.25,0:03:34.97,Chinese,,0,0,0,,这里还有八页的附加手册，上面有DOS相关的安装提示
Dialogue: 0,0:03:34.97,0:03:37.59,Chinese,,0,0,0,,和一些疑难解答
Dialogue: 0,0:03:37.59,0:03:43.39,Chinese,,0,0,0,,然后就是14页全彩的游戏手册，包括背景故事
Dialogue: 0,0:03:43.39,0:03:47.97,Chinese,,0,0,0,,游戏贴士，和游戏中所遇到的武器，物品和敌人介绍
Dialogue: 0,0:03:47.97,0:03:51.74,Chinese,,0,0,0,,东西很好，但是我欲火焚身，所以咱来一局吧:-D
Dialogue: 0,0:03:52.30,0:03:58.84,Chinese,,0,0,0,,DOS版《毁灭战士》启动后，和前代一样，仍是生动的256色图片
Dialogue: 0,0:03:58.84,0:04:03.08,Chinese,,0,0,0,,上面描绘着恶魔毁灭世界的场景，伴随着不祥的音乐
Dialogue: 0,0:04:10.84,0:04:12.36,Chinese,,0,0,0,,这个只是声霸卡合成版
Dialogue: 0,0:04:12.36,0:04:16.22,Chinese,,0,0,0,,当然，这个还支持Roland Sound Canvas和其他的MIDI合成设备
Dialogue: 0,0:04:16.22,0:04:18.42,Chinese,,0,0,0,,但是《毁灭战士》游戏和
Dialogue: 0,0:04:18.42,0:04:20.96,Chinese,,0,0,0,,Bobby Prince编的吓人OPL3音乐
Dialogue: 0,0:04:20.96,0:04:22.66,Chinese,,0,0,0,,让我金属的内心受到了滋润
Dialogue: 0,0:04:22.66,0:04:27.34,Chinese,,0,0,0,,在这里你可以开局新游戏，然后选个难度......然后就享受吧！
Dialogue: 0,0:04:27.34,0:04:32.36,Chinese,,0,0,0,,这回咱不用选章节了，你要一口气打连续的30个关卡
Dialogue: 0,0:04:32.36,0:04:36.94,Chinese,,0,0,0,,开局相当直接，手里有把枪，准备打僵尸
Dialogue: 0,0:04:44.36,0:04:48.14,Chinese,,0,0,0,,或者你可以花点时间，看看周围，探索环境
Dialogue: 0,0:04:48.15,0:04:52.81,Chinese,,0,0,0,,很快你就会发现后面的过道右面藏着个电锯
Dialogue: 0,0:04:52.81,0:04:55.04,Chinese,,0,0,0,,是的，我是电锯的忠实拥趸
Dialogue: 0,0:05:03.42,0:05:07.40,Chinese,,0,0,0,,如果你足够细心电话，第一关通关时，你会有一个电锯
Dialogue: 0,0:05:07.40,0:05:11.30,Chinese,,0,0,0,,一把猎枪，一个火箭发射器，一些护甲，还有满血
Dialogue: 0,0:05:11.30,0:05:16.38,Chinese,,0,0,0,,第一关你就武装到了牙齿，那下面的关卡自然不在话下啦
Dialogue: 0,0:05:18.42,0:05:23.04,Chinese,,0,0,0,,你已经准备好开始你的地狱受虐之旅，Doomguy快速又敏捷地奔跑
Dialogue: 0,0:05:23.04,0:05:27.94,Chinese,,0,0,0,,而且玩这个游戏的手感和原版《毁灭战士》简直是一模一样
Dialogue: 0,0:05:27.94,0:05:32.75,Chinese,,0,0,0,,谁让《毁灭战士二代》和前代用的技术是一样的呢？而且这个基本上
Dialogue: 0,0:05:32.75,0:05:34.62,Chinese,,0,0,0,,就是原版游戏的扩充包呢
Dialogue: 0,0:05:34.62,0:05:40.28,Chinese,,0,0,0,,它的底层同样使用2.5D id Tech 1 游戏引擎，而且同样地
Dialogue: 0,0:05:40.28,0:05:43.74,Chinese,,0,0,0,,不能上下看，或者屋子和屋子相连
Dialogue: 0,0:05:43.74,0:05:45.94,Chinese,,0,0,0,,没有跳跃，没有垂直瞄准
Dialogue: 0,0:05:45.94,0:05:49.00,Chinese,,0,0,0,,没有什么特殊方式跳关或者解锁能力树啥的
Dialogue: 0,0:05:49.00,0:05:51.52,Chinese,,0,0,0,,而这些在我而言，都是非常不错的
Dialogue: 0,0:05:51.52,0:05:57.16,Chinese,,0,0,0,,杀掉敌人，找到钥匙，解锁秘密之处，然后找更多的钥匙
Dialogue: 0,0:05:57.16,0:06:01.59,Chinese,,0,0,0,,来解锁开关，进入下一关卡，如此下去，直到看见最终BOSS
Dialogue: 0,0:06:01.59,0:06:04.90,Chinese,,0,0,0,,既然FPS已经发展的那么好了，那这还能发展什么呢？
Dialogue: 0,0:06:05.18,0:06:09.32,Chinese,,0,0,0,,我猜，他们可以设计更多的枪来解决
Dialogue: 0,0:06:09.32,0:06:11.78,Chinese,,0,0,0,,毕竟这个游戏是在德州开发的，对吧
Dialogue: 0,0:06:09.32,0:06:11.78,Comments,,0,0,0,,注：来自德州的神奇科技 {\fnComic Sans MS\fs55}BV1Dz4y1Q7ba@David Murray & Woodear
Dialogue: 0,0:06:11.78,0:06:17.56,Chinese,,0,0,0,,现在我要给大家展示《毁灭战士》的超强军械库了，绝对让您爱不释手
Dialogue: 0,0:06:17.56,0:06:22.18,Chinese,,0,0,0,,抛去上回说到的锯子，手枪，猎枪和火箭发射器以外
Dialogue: 0,0:06:22.18,0:06:27.43,Chinese,,0,0,0,,还有最好用的常胜将军机关枪，能够快速扫荡整个屋子
Dialogue: 0,0:06:27.43,0:06:30.69,Chinese,,0,0,0,,无论近战还是远战，都是得力助手
Dialogue: 0,0:06:30.69,0:06:35.61,Chinese,,0,0,0,,当然，这里还有等离子枪，打出等离子的速度和原版一样
Dialogue: 0,0:06:35.61,0:06:38.74,Chinese,,0,0,0,,但是出现的时间比之前更早，就在第五个地图上
Dialogue: 0,0:06:38.74,0:06:43.38,Chinese,,0,0,0,,当然，没有BFG的《毁灭战士》是称不上《毁灭战士》的
Dialogue: 0,0:06:43.38,0:06:47.12,Chinese,,0,0,0,,但是这回它的出现时间更早了，在第八关拿到后
Dialogue: 0,0:06:47.12,0:06:49.52,Chinese,,0,0,0,,你就可以开始你的等离子屠杀计划啦:-D
Dialogue: 0,0:06:49.52,0:06:52.14,Chinese,,0,0,0,,然后......等会！还有！
Dialogue: 0,0:06:52.14,0:06:56.06,Chinese,,0,0,0,,还有那个一直被模仿，从未被超越的
Dialogue: 0,0:06:56.06,0:06:58.04,Chinese,,0,0,0,,双管超级猎枪
Dialogue: 0,0:07:07.10,0:07:10.90,Chinese,,0,0,0,,你在第二关就会发现，然后当你用过这个怪兽般的武器后
Dialogue: 0,0:07:10.90,0:07:13.04,Chinese,,0,0,0,,你就会感受到刘备得到诸葛亮时如鱼得水的快乐了
Dialogue: 0,0:07:13.04,0:07:16.91,Chinese,,0,0,0,,虽然它比单管猎枪要多用双倍的子弹，但是这可是
Dialogue: 0,0:07:16.91,0:07:21.30,Chinese,,0,0,0,,比单管枪多了不知多少倍的快乐啊！那这交易不就值了吗:-)
Dialogue: 0,0:07:21.30,0:07:25.24,Chinese,,0,0,0,,仅仅是把两个枪管用一个木枪托合在一处，再装点弹药
Dialogue: 0,0:07:25.24,0:07:29.72,Chinese,,0,0,0,,也许长了张猴子脸，但是一棒子就能能结果了你
Dialogue: 0,0:07:29.72,0:07:33.93,Chinese,,0,0,0,,往往都是由它来打出致命一击，而这就够了
Dialogue: 0,0:07:33.93,0:07:36.74,Chinese,,0,0,0,,打战役的时候，这就是常态
Dialogue: 0,0:07:38.06,0:07:40.12,Chinese,,0,0,0,,这也就是为什么这个叫：超级猎枪
Dialogue: 0,0:07:40.12,0:07:41.66,Chinese,,0,0,0,,因为它可是耐人啊！
Dialogue: 0,0:07:41.66,0:07:44.30,Chinese,,0,0,0,,尽管我认为实际上这个应该称为：战斗猎枪
Dialogue: 0,0:07:44.30,0:07:46.90,Chinese,,0,0,0,,至少在手册中是这样写的，但是
Dialogue: 0,0:07:46.90,0:07:51.02,Chinese,,0,0,0,,额，这至少让我想到一堆半自动枪和全自动枪
Dialogue: 0,0:07:51.03,0:07:56.15,Chinese,,0,0,0,,所以我在游戏中看到更合适的“超级猎枪”名字，感觉更加亲切
Dialogue: 0,0:07:56.15,0:08:00.02,Chinese,,0,0,0,,还有一点，超强的新武器那一定得有更厉害的妖魔鬼怪
Dialogue: 0,0:08:00.02,0:08:01.50,Chinese,,0,0,0,,来展示出它的魅力啊
Dialogue: 0,0:08:01.50,0:08:05.91,Chinese,,0,0,0,,原版《毁灭战士》的十个怪兽当然还在这里腻味你们
Dialogue: 0,0:08:05.91,0:08:09.91,Chinese,,0,0,0,,包括你很熟悉的Cyberdemon，原版是Boss，现在
Dialogue: 0,0:08:05.91,0:08:09.91,Comments,,0,0,0,,注：DOOM永恒称为暴君
Dialogue: 0,0:08:09.91,0:08:11.65,Chinese,,0,0,0,,它在这里专门腻味你，阻止你通关
Dialogue: 0,0:08:11.65,0:08:16.37,Chinese,,0,0,0,,但是《毁灭战士二代》还特意添加更多敌人来进一步恶心你
Dialogue: 0,0:08:16.37,0:08:18.54,Chinese,,0,0,0,,让你觉得敌人团结起来，更加强大
Dialogue: 0,0:08:18.54,0:08:22.69,Chinese,,0,0,0,,重机枪僵尸装备了机关枪，当你疏忽的时候
Dialogue: 0,0:08:22.69,0:08:25.30,Chinese,,0,0,0,,他们分分钟就能让你去当太虚幻境的门卫，他们的连击武器可不认人的
Dialogue: 0,0:08:25.30,0:08:29.78,Chinese,,0,0,0,,地狱骑士就像是恐惧骑士的缩水版
Dialogue: 0,0:08:29.78,0:08:32.14,Chinese,,0,0,0,,没啥可怕的，你就当他们在插标卖首就好啦:-)
Dialogue: 0,0:08:32.14,0:08:37.06,Chinese,,0,0,0,,生化肥球如名所示，可以一次射出两大火球，立马将你搞死
Dialogue: 0,0:08:37.06,0:08:39.30,Chinese,,0,0,0,,虽然很慢，但是很腻味人
Dialogue: 0,0:08:39.30,0:08:44.14,Chinese,,0,0,0,,蜘蛛怪是上代机械蜘蛛的缩水版，这个更小而且
Dialogue: 0,0:08:44.14,0:08:47.78,Chinese,,0,0,0,,可以射出绿色能量波，幸亏处理起来相当容易
Dialogue: 0,0:08:47.78,0:08:53.19,Chinese,,0,0,0,,还有痛苦元素，本体就是鸡肋，就像是另一个漂浮怪兽巨脑魔
Dialogue: 0,0:08:53.19,0:08:56.39,Chinese,,0,0,0,,但是这个不吐红色闪电，而是丧魂
Dialogue: 0,0:08:56.39,0:08:59.58,Chinese,,0,0,0,,所以这个解决起来很麻烦，真是个痛苦......
Dialogue: 0,0:08:59.92,0:09:00.86,Chinese,,0,0,0,,元素:-(
Dialogue: 0,0:09:00.86,0:09:04.14,Chinese,,0,0,0,,然后是骷髅兵，一个拥有硕大笨重骨架的打怪物
Dialogue: 0,0:09:04.14,0:09:07.02,Chinese,,0,0,0,,肩膀上帮着火箭发射器，让所有前世伤害它的人血债血偿
Dialogue: 0,0:09:07.02,0:09:11.28,Chinese,,0,0,0,,消灭起来倒是容易，但是值得注意的是，他带的火箭发射器的伤害很大
Dialogue: 0,0:09:11.28,0:09:16.46,Chinese,,0,0,0,,终于，这里还有个极其难缠的大家伙————召唤师
Dialogue: 0,0:09:16.46,0:09:19.94,Chinese,,0,0,0,,不光看上去很可怕，而且看上去很致命:-(
Dialogue: 0,0:09:19.94,0:09:23.87,Chinese,,0,0,0,,仅仅是与他对视，你就会引火烧身
Dialogue: 0,0:09:23.87,0:09:26.70,Chinese,,0,0,0,,直到你从地狱直升天堂，这可真是够恶心的
Dialogue: 0,0:09:26.70,0:09:31.14,Chinese,,0,0,0,,如果战斗相持很久的话，它能将死去的敌人续上一命
Dialogue: 0,0:09:31.14,0:09:32.77,Chinese,,0,0,0,,所以见到它，一定要速战速决
Dialogue: 0,0:09:32.77,0:09:34.52,Chinese,,0,0,0,,刀起刀落间，就置其于死地
Dialogue: 0,0:09:34.52,0:09:38.88,Chinese,,0,0,0,,当然，这里还有两个秘密关卡，包括可以杀掉的
Dialogue: 0,0:09:34.52,0:09:38.88,Comments,,0,0,0,,注：德国版由于涉及纳粹标志，故没有包含
Dialogue: 0,0:09:38.88,0:09:42.83,Chinese,,0,0,0,,上吊的Commander Keens, 甚至还有《德军总部3D》的党卫军
Dialogue: 0,0:09:38.88,0:09:42.83,Comments,,0,0,0,,注：《Commander Keen（指挥官基恩）》和《德军总部3D》均为id Software开发
Dialogue: 0,0:09:42.83,0:09:47.16,Chinese,,0,0,0,,但这个更像是彩蛋之类的东西，你绝对不会在
Dialogue: 0,0:09:47.16,0:09:50.90,Chinese,,0,0,0,,火星上的太空基地上看见指挥官和纳粹走狗
Dialogue: 0,0:09:50.90,0:09:55.46,Chinese,,0,0,0,,说到这个，我还想谈论一下这个游戏总共30个关卡的设计，
Dialogue: 0,0:09:55.46,0:09:59.13,Chinese,,0,0,0,,氛围的设定，还有整个的节奏
Dialogue: 0,0:09:59.13,0:10:04.16,Chinese,,0,0,0,,因为呢......《毁灭战士二代》要我说就像是水泊梁山
Dialogue: 0,0:10:04.16,0:10:06.52,Chinese,,0,0,0,,不是通俗的意思，那些好汉都是遵纪守法的
Dialogue: 0,0:10:06.52,0:10:09.04,Chinese,,0,0,0,,找他们帮忙不仅和气相待，而且不会闹得官府想方设法招安
Dialogue: 0,0:10:09.04,0:10:13.70,Chinese,,0,0,0,,只不过这些好汉里有几个长得很可疑
Dialogue: 0,0:10:13.70,0:10:16.64,Chinese,,0,0,0,,让你觉得他们有点黑
Dialogue: 0,0:09:59.13,0:10:16.64,Comments,,0,0,0,,注：原意为这个游戏像锅大杂烩，虽然好玩，但是总有几处让你想不明白
Dialogue: 0,0:10:16.64,0:10:21.49,Chinese,,0,0,0,,我最大的疑惑是这个游戏大约四分之一的关卡不太吸引我
Dialogue: 0,0:10:21.49,0:10:24.62,Chinese,,0,0,0,,尤其是那些本应该基于我们日常生活的关卡
Dialogue: 0,0:10:24.62,0:10:29.70,Chinese,,0,0,0,,你看啊，这个副标题叫“地狱上凡”，好歹人间烟火得更多些吧
Dialogue: 0,0:10:29.70,0:10:31.20,Chinese,,0,0,0,,然后再穿插几个地狱关卡
Dialogue: 0,0:10:31.20,0:10:35.32,Chinese,,0,0,0,,然而我们玩到的是互相衔接比较松散的几个关卡
Dialogue: 0,0:10:35.33,0:10:39.38,Chinese,,0,0,0,,大致分为三个部分：太空基地，街头混战，地狱之战
Dialogue: 0,0:10:39.38,0:10:44.02,Chinese,,0,0,0,,再次强调，这个游戏的大多数关卡都十分有趣，我更是反复把玩的
Dialogue: 0,0:10:44.02,0:10:48.27,Chinese,,0,0,0,,火星上的太空基地和像素化的地狱......小二，再上几关！
Dialogue: 0,0:10:48.27,0:10:52.88,Chinese,,0,0,0,,当你打到诸如市中心关（第十三关）时......这玩意是嘛？
Dialogue: 0,0:10:52.88,0:10:54.90,Chinese,,0,0,0,,也许我在尝试一些新的东西吧
Dialogue: 0,0:10:54.90,0:10:58.96,Chinese,,0,0,0,,DOOM引擎里的大都市和摩天大楼画得倒是不错
Dialogue: 0,0:10:58.96,0:11:04.10,Chinese,,0,0,0,,但是这也是战斗的号角，而且你满目之下，全是妖怪:-(
Dialogue: 0,0:11:04.10,0:11:08.93,Chinese,,0,0,0,,也有些地图专门画得很大来炫耀他们精巧的设计，诸如
Dialogue: 0,0:11:08.93,0:11:11.67,Chinese,,0,0,0,,捉迷藏（第八关），鸿沟（第二十四关）和油桶连环炸（第二十三关）
Dialogue: 0,0:11:11.67,0:11:16.20,Chinese,,0,0,0,,诸如怪兽窝里斗，传送带神用途，恶心的平台，极细的过道
Dialogue: 0,0:11:16.20,0:11:20.88,Chinese,,0,0,0,,好几百个油桶放一块，我们不是卡在了张飞虐兵实验所了吧？
Dialogue: 0,0:11:20.88,0:11:24.28,Chinese,,0,0,0,,这样的关卡十分怪异，从头到尾都很难
Dialogue: 0,0:11:24.28,0:11:28.26,Chinese,,0,0,0,,在这我就不让设计这些关卡的人拉出来公开处刑了{\fnComic Sans MS\fs75}(Sandy Petersen)
Dialogue: 0,0:11:24.28,0:11:28.26,Comments,,0,0,0,,{\fnComic Sans MS\fs60}Sandy: {\fn文泉驿等宽微米黑\fs50}海绵宝宝，我找你找的好苦啊！来，咱们到针堆里找松树叶吧:-)
Dialogue: 0,0:11:28.26,0:11:32.61,Chinese,,0,0,0,,但是我这几年来越是仔细把玩，越是听见就害怕
Dialogue: 0,0:11:32.61,0:11:35.10,Chinese,,0,0,0,,当然，这也不是说这些新地图都是平庸之作
Dialogue: 0,0:11:35.10,0:11:40.38,Chinese,,0,0,0,,这些关卡比初版《毁灭战士》更具实验性，怪兽们在开阔的场地里聚集
Dialogue: 0,0:11:40.38,0:11:44.83,Chinese,,0,0,0,,从而有一些超级扯淡的关卡，你会在和怪兽周旋时看见他们互相攻击
Dialogue: 0,0:11:44.83,0:11:48.70,Chinese,,0,0,0,,哀嚎不止，以至于混乱中内斗，咱们就等着渔翁得利吧:-)
Dialogue: 0,0:12:03.26,0:12:08.17,Chinese,,0,0,0,,而这些又大又复杂的关卡的一大副作用就是
Dialogue: 0,0:12:08.17,0:12:12.61,Chinese,,0,0,0,,在发行时的1994年，低端电脑的表现不佳，进而
Dialogue: 0,0:12:12.61,0:12:13.88,Chinese,,0,0,0,,对《毁灭战士二代》的系统要求就更高了
Dialogue: 0,0:12:13.88,0:12:17.30,Chinese,,0,0,0,,所以咱必须装个486 Overdrive，对吧
Dialogue: 0,0:12:13.88,0:12:17.30,Comments,,0,0,0,,注：BV1XE411M7dw 更换一块83MHz的奔腾OverDrive CPU @ LGR & 某科学的小姚同志\N
Dialogue: 0,0:12:17.30,0:12:22.04,Chinese,,0,0,0,,有些地方黑暗的角度十分怪异，从而营造出一种合适的
Dialogue: 0,0:12:22.04,0:12:25.92,Chinese,,0,0,0,,恐怖气氛，从而让夜视镜的存在
Dialogue: 0,0:12:25.92,0:12:27.94,Chinese,,0,0,0,,变得更加合理
Dialogue: 0,0:12:27.94,0:12:32.83,Chinese,,0,0,0,,然而，这个并不会让你的增强火力变得更加厉害
Dialogue: 0,0:12:32.83,0:12:36.82,Chinese,,0,0,0,,更不用说新加的可以将护甲和生命都加到200%的超次元球
Dialogue: 0,0:12:36.82,0:12:40.20,Chinese,,0,0,0,,当然，环境确实很黑，但还没让你觉得不公平
Dialogue: 0,0:12:40.20,0:12:44.62,Chinese,,0,0,0,,无论如何，尽管经常遇见的地图难题很让人抓狂
Dialogue: 0,0:12:44.62,0:12:48.26,Chinese,,0,0,0,,但是我玩《毁灭战士二代》时的体验还是令我珍惜的
Dialogue: 0,0:12:48.26,0:12:52.08,Chinese,,0,0,0,,而且我确实认为超级猎枪确实能立大功
Dialogue: 0,0:12:52.08,0:12:54.42,Chinese,,0,0,0,,即使它功力确实被夸大了
Dialogue: 0,0:12:54.42,0:12:57.18,Chinese,,0,0,0,,但是我还是十分喜欢用的！
Dialogue: 0,0:12:57.18,0:13:00.77,Chinese,,0,0,0,,也许咱改天再提多人死亡生存模式吧
Dialogue: 0,0:13:00.77,0:13:04.31,Chinese,,0,0,0,,因为咱今天主要提的是单人游戏，那咱就光说这个吧
Dialogue: 0,0:13:04.31,0:13:09.24,Chinese,,0,0,0,,然后你就买到了更多的怪兽和更多的火力
Dialogue: 0,0:13:09.24,0:13:12.95,Chinese,,0,0,0,,难怪《毁灭战士二代》比一代的影响力更大
Dialogue: 0,0:13:12.95,0:13:17.63,Chinese,,0,0,0,,显然，我要说的是社区的活跃度，而不是说大量的安装量
Dialogue: 0,0:13:17.63,0:13:19.49,Chinese,,0,0,0,,或者说整体的文化氛围
Dialogue: 0,0:13:19.49,0:13:24.73,Chinese,,0,0,0,,显然原版《毁灭战士》在历史上有着浓厚一笔，但是
Dialogue: 0,0:13:24.73,0:13:27.83,Chinese,,0,0,0,,《毁灭战士二代》的浓厚文化圈子到现在还很活跃
Dialogue: 0,0:13:27.83,0:13:32.74,Chinese,,0,0,0,,数量众多的自制地图和WAD在现在看来仍然是很惊人的
Dialogue: 0,0:13:32.74,0:13:35.01,Chinese,,0,0,0,,无论是在当时还是在现在
Dialogue: 0,0:13:35.01,0:13:39.99,Chinese,,0,0,0,,而在《毁灭战士》的引擎在1997年开源以后，对游戏的定制就更多了
Dialogue: 0,0:13:39.99,0:13:45.38,Chinese,,0,0,0,,然后就有了GLDoom，ZDoom，Boom，Chocolate Doom
Dialogue: 0,0:13:45.38,0:13:47.80,Chinese,,0,0,0,,Skulltag, Zandronum之类的改进引擎
Dialogue: 0,0:13:47.80,0:13:52.02,Chinese,,0,0,0,,当我需要在现代电脑而不是古董机上打游戏时，我十分喜欢用
Dialogue: 0,0:13:52.02,0:13:56.31,Chinese,,0,0,0,,Crispy Doom，因为这个可以在不破坏
Dialogue: 0,0:13:56.31,0:13:59.33,Chinese,,0,0,0,,原版游戏体验的情况下提升了性能和功能
Dialogue: 0,0:13:59.33,0:14:04.01,Chinese,,0,0,0,,再提销售方面，在1994年《毁灭战士二代》发行后
Dialogue: 0,0:14:04.01,0:14:06.85,Chinese,,0,0,0,,各种针对其的插件和扩展就一直充斥着市场
Dialogue: 0,0:14:06.85,0:14:13.29,Chinese,,0,0,0,,而官方也在1995年发行了《毁灭战士二代大师关卡》，包括
Dialogue: 0,0:14:13.29,0:14:17.18,Chinese,,0,0,0,,二十个游戏大师设计的关卡和多达三千个从网上下载的
Dialogue: 0,0:14:17.18,0:14:19.24,Chinese,,0,0,0,,由粉丝制作的关卡
Dialogue: 0,0:14:19.24,0:14:23.46,Chinese,,0,0,0,,还有这个超大的海报，将盒子上画的东西给放大了
Dialogue: 0,0:14:23.47,0:14:28.82,Chinese,,0,0,0,,然后就是1996年发行的《最后的毁灭战士》，一个官方授权产品
Dialogue: 0,0:14:28.82,0:14:32.74,Chinese,,0,0,0,,包括两个新战役：TNT: Evilution 和 Plutonia Experiment
Dialogue: 0,0:14:32.74,0:14:36.46,Chinese,,0,0,0,,当然，这和真正的结尾还差很远呢
Dialogue: 0,0:14:36.46,0:14:42.62,Chinese,,0,0,0,,因为1997年他们还发行了the Depths of Doom Trilogy
Dialogue: 0,0:14:42.62,0:14:45.11,Chinese,,0,0,0,,大箱子里面包含一二代《毁灭战士》和《大师关卡》
Dialogue: 0,0:14:45.11,0:14:48.98,Chinese,,0,0,0,,当然，之后还有一大堆重新发行，其中最有意思的
Dialogue: 0,0:14:48.98,0:14:54.62,Chinese,,0,0,0,,是Xbox 360版，里面有No Rest For The Living，由
Dialogue: 0,0:14:54.62,0:14:57.26,Chinese,,0,0,0,,Nerve Software制作的全新战役
Dialogue: 0,0:14:57.26,0:14:59.74,Chinese,,0,0,0,,说真的，这玩意还行，我十分推荐！
Dialogue: 0,0:14:59.75,0:15:04.52,Chinese,,0,0,0,,这个后来附加在《毁灭战士3》BFG版本里，当然里面也有
Dialogue: 0,0:15:04.52,0:15:09.60,Chinese,,0,0,0,,《毁灭战士二代》，而且你也可以在有合适WAD的情况下，找个引擎玩
Dialogue: 0,0:15:09.60,0:15:14.48,Chinese,,0,0,0,,当然各种非授权产品就更多了，各种第三方公司，诸如WizardWorks
Dialogue: 0,0:15:14.48,0:15:20.67,Chinese,,0,0,0,,从1995年开始，已经发行了至少半打称为D!Zone系列的地图集
Dialogue: 0,0:15:20.67,0:15:25.85,Chinese,,0,0,0,,《毁灭战士二代》在整个九十年代都有自己的游戏生态
Dialogue: 0,0:15:25.85,0:15:29.75,Chinese,,0,0,0,,店里有买的，朋友间也会共享，甚至美国政府也插了一脚
Dialogue: 0,0:15:29.75,0:15:32.48,Chinese,,0,0,0,,是的，我说的就是Marine Doom，一个由
Dialogue: 0,0:15:32.48,0:15:36.48,Chinese,,0,0,0,,美国海军陆战队建模仿真实验室开发的关卡
Dialogue: 0,0:15:36.48,0:15:39.36,Chinese,,0,0,0,,呵呵，九十年代真可是疯狂的年代:-P
Dialogue: 0,0:15:40.22,0:15:42.52,Chinese,,0,0,0,,好了，老哥儿，这就是《毁灭战士二代》啦
Dialogue: 0,0:15:42.92,0:15:47.20,Chinese,,0,0,0,,这个游戏虽然是在见钱眼开的发行商催的情况下
Dialogue: 0,0:15:47.20,0:15:49.30,Chinese,,0,0,0,,在少于一年的工期内赶出来的
Dialogue: 0,0:15:49.30,0:15:53.51,Chinese,,0,0,0,,是的，也许这个游戏会很差，但是在当时，id Software已经
Dialogue: 0,0:15:53.51,0:15:56.58,Chinese,,0,0,0,,尽力做了，而且在满足条件的情况下，还更上一层楼
Dialogue: 0,0:15:56.58,0:16:01.70,Chinese,,0,0,0,,据我看来，《毁灭战士二代》继承了原版的游戏结构之类
Dialogue: 0,0:16:01.70,0:16:03.64,Chinese,,0,0,0,,而且充实了游戏内容并扩大了名声
Dialogue: 0,0:16:03.64,0:16:08.14,Chinese,,0,0,0,,天知道要是没有骷髅兵和超级猎枪的话，这个游戏将会如何
Dialogue: 0,0:16:08.14,0:16:12.22,Chinese,,0,0,0,,或者射击一墙大的怪兽，实际上后面是立在木桩上的John Romero之头
Dialogue: 0,0:16:12.22,0:16:18.24,Chinese,,0,0,0,,而且在当时之后的一段时间内，这类游戏很难找到，而且搞到一份也是很值了
Dialogue: 0,0:16:18.24,0:16:21.85,Chinese,,0,0,0,,《毁灭战士二代》让毁灭战士更像毁灭战士了
Dialogue: 0,0:16:21.86,0:16:24.54,Chinese,,0,0,0,,虽白璧微瑕，我还是很喜欢
